On Sat, 06 Jun 2026 09:29:09 GMT Marcin Mermela wrote:
> Dear TinyAdz Support & Compliance Team,
I am writing to formally address =
serious discrepancies in the reporting and
payout metrics on my publisher =
dashboard for the website void.skyreel.art.=20
Upon auditing our internal =
analytics and comparing your network=E2=80=99s performance
with other tier-1 ad networks (such as Monetag), we have identified several
highly concerning patterns that suggest potential violations of transparent
advertising standards and fair business practices.
1. Unexplained Data =
Discrepancies:
Your dashboard reports a total of 99,068 views and 5,009 =
verified clicks,
resulting in $47.47 in estimated earnings. However, the =
sum of all individual
banners listed on the same page (Custom Inlined Ad, =
Corner Mini Pop-Up, and
Full-screen Banner) accounts for only 26,825 views =
and $12.74 in earnings. There
is an unaccounted gap of 72,243 views and $34=
.73 in earnings that is completely
missing from the breakdown. Please =
explain why this data is hidden and how these
figures are calculated.
2. Retroactive Click Deductions ("Shaving"):
Your FAQ openly states: "Why =
do clicks sometimes decrease when I refresh the
page?" Retroactively =
deducting already registered "verified" clicks is a highly
questionable practice often associated with "click shaving". Under standard
publisher transparency rules, we request a detailed, timestamped log of all
deducted clicks, including the specific reasons and IP addresses classified=
 as
invalid.
3. Extremely Low CPM/CPC Rates:
Our current stats show an =
average CPM of $0.48 and a CPC of $0.009 per verified
click. In comparison, our alternative network (Monetag) yields a CPM of $3.=
18
for the same traffic=E2=80=94over 6.6x higher. A CPC under 1 cent for =
verified user
clicks is statistically anomalous and indicates either a =
severe mispricing or a
massive revenue-share imbalance.
4. Arbitrary Earning Caps:
We note that our account has an artificial limit=
 of "capped at $432/month".
Placing arbitrary caps on traffic monetization =
without prior agreement is an
unfair trade restriction.
We request a formal audit report of our account=E2=80=99s traffic from your=
 quality
assurance department within 7 business days, including:
- A complete breakdown of the unaccounted 72,243 views.
- Full details on the "Tier 29" classification and how to remove it.
- Traffic logs explaining any click deductions.
Should we not receive a =
transparent explanation, we will be forced to terminate
our partnership, move all remaining slots to Monetag, and file official
complaints with relevant advertising standards authorities and consumer
protection bodies.
We expect your prompt response.
